# Command: node dist/cli/main.js --help

Usage: autonomous-dev-homelab [options] [command]

Homelab platform discovery, connection, and lifecycle automation.

Options:
  --data-dir <path>             directory for consent + inventory state files
  -h, --help                    display help for command

Commands:
  discover [options]            Probe a CIDR range for known homelab platforms.
  platform                      Per-platform CA install, connection check, and
                                key rotation.
  audit                         Verify and query the homelab audit log.
  consent                       List, grant, or revoke per-CIDR network scan
                                consents.
  ca                            SSH certificate-authority lifecycle (init,
                                rotate, list).
  observe                       Run probes, list observations, or manually
                                promote one to autonomous-dev intake.
  safety                        Inspect safety attributes of pending actions.
  cancel-action [options] <id>  Cancel a pending architectural-action delay.
  migrations                    Inspect homelab migration state.
  metrics                       Inspect homelab safety + observability metrics.
  portal [options]              Open the homelab portal panel in the operator
                                browser.
  config                        Config management.
  vault                         Vault integration commands.
  autofix                       Manage autofix proposals and actions.
  connect                       Test connectivity to homelab hosts via MCP or
                                SSH.
  inventory                     Read or manage the discovered-platforms
                                inventory.
  help [command]                display help for command

